<br>
1) Summoning a pet is not a habit for me. In fact, especially in dungeons I will check with the group leader when they want the pet summoned. Most of the time its not until the camp site is reached.<br>
2) If a mage looses a pet, he goes and finds it, away from the group and dies where his pet dies to preserve the group.<br>
3) And as for pets breaking mez, just poor pet control once again. But this is the more difficult situation for a mage to control and one of the things mages are asking Verant to fix, probably with a new pet command where the pet will simply stop fighting back, eg /pet no attack. This way a mob can just beat on the pet but under no circumstance will the pet fight back.<br>
For me at the moment I have to mash my /pet back off button until the enchanter can mez the mob so it stops attacking the pet and the pet wont feel inclined to fight back and break mez again. Its kind of like a chicken &amp; egg situation. (probably havent described that too well).<br>
<br>
I hate solo'ing, its boring and lame and theres more XP to be had in groups, more interesting people to meet, and exciting monsters to slay. <p>cheers<BR>
